      "date": "2011-06-17 18:16:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nLooks fine in this case.\n\nAs a minor side note, not all cases where there are broken lines need escapes for the EOL.  Where the shell clearly knows there is more input required, it doesn't:\n\n     ls -l $SOME_LONG_DIRECTORY_NAME |\n        grep -q \"foo\" &&\n        echo \"fooey directory\"\n\nwill work just fine.",
